olo in the 1945 film [[The Stork Club (1945 film)|''The Stork Club'']] ]]\n\n[[File:Andy Russell and Betty Hutton sing \"If I had a Dozen Hearts\".ogv|thumb|Andy Russell and Betty Hutton sing a duet:  \"If I had a Dozen Hearts\" in the 1945 film ''The Stork Club'']]\n\n[[File:Andy Russell Sings Love Me from the 1945 film The Stork Club.ogv|thumb|Andy Russell sings \"Love Me\" in the 1945 film ''[[The Stork Club (1945 film)|The Stork Club]]'']]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 1946 || ''[[Breakfast in Hollywood (film)|Breakfast in Hollywood]]'' || Singer || Directed by [[Harold D. Schuster]].\n\nSings \"If I Had a Wishing Ring,\" \"[[Mar\u00eda Grever|Magic Is the Moonlight / \"Te quiero, dijiste (Mu\u00f1equita linda)\"]],\" and \"[[Amor (1943 song)|Amor]]\"\n\n[[File:Andy Russell - If I Had a Wishing Ring 1946.ogv|thumb|Andy Russell sings \"If I Had a Wishing Ring\" in ''Breakfast in Hollywood'' (1946)]]\n\n[[File:Andy Russell - Magic Is the Moonlight 1946 from Breakfast in Hollywood.ogv|thumb|Andy Russell sings \"Magic Is the Moonlight\"/\"Te quiero dijiste (Mu\u00f1equita linda)\" in ''Breakfast in Hollywood'' (1946)]]\n\n[[File:Andy Russell Sings \"Amor\" in \"Breakfast in Hollywood\" (1946).ogv|thumb|Andy Russell Sings \"Amor\" in ''Breakfast in Hollywood ''(1946)]]\n\n|-\n|[[Walt Disney]]'s ''[[Make Mine Music]]'' (Animation) || Voice || Sings \"Without You\" (\"Tres Palabras\")  \n|-\n| 1947 || ''[[Copacabana (1947 film)|Copacabana]]'' || Singer || Directed by [[Alfred E. Green]].\n\nSings \"My Heart Was Doing a Bolero,\" \"Stranger Things Have Happened,\" \"He Hasn't Got a thing to Sell,\" and \"Je Vous Aime.\"\n|-\n| 1953 || ''House Party (Short)'' || Singer ||  Co-stars with his wife Della.\n\nThey sang \"Don't Say Hello,\" \"Just the Two of Us,\" \"Sweet and Lovely,\" and \"You Could Be Replaced.\"\n\n|-\n| 1955 || ''\u00a1Qu\u00e9 bravas son las coste\u00f1as!'' (Coastal women are so temperamental!) || Tony L\u00f3pez ||  Mexican production, directed by [[Roberto R